# Bug: a method with a concrete reference return type but an Object-typed value at the return site
# (erased generic / try-with-resources null-only slot) rendered `return objVar;`, which javac rejects
# as "incompatible types: Object cannot be converted to <T>" -- a real tree-recompile / repackage
# blocker (the fastjson2 JSON.parseObject/parseArray family: 21 errors).
#
# Seed: synthetic `static String first(String)` whose try-with-resources `return null` desugars to a
# slot the decompiler reconstructs as `Object varN = null; return varN`. Fix: objectReturnDowncast
# emits the legal, behavior-preserving `(String)` downcast (Object is the supertype of every ref
# type, so the cast always compiles; matches CFR/Fernflower). Kill-switch JDEC_OBJECT_RET_DOWNCAST_OFF
# restores the legacy uncast emission (see TestReturnObjectDowncastIsLoadBearing).
#
# The Object-typed null slot is returned with an explicit downcast to the declared return type.
+/return \(String\) \(var\d+\);/
# The already-correctly-typed (String) slot must NOT be over-cast.
+/return var\d+_\d+;/
